The paper focuses on the collection and analysis of data related to Internet malicious activity, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to classify reported activities, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper analyzes the temporal behavior of mal-activity reporting, which could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses various datasets and leverages the Wayback Machine, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
